 flour, eggs and 1 tbsp olive oil in mixing bowl then knead <b>2 min\/<b>. Dough will appear crumbly."},{"content":"Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or floured work surface and work into a ball. Wrap dough in cling film, then leave to rest for 15 minutes. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Using a rolling pin or pasta machine, roll out dough until 2 mm in thickness. Sprinkle extra flour onto pasta to prevent it from sticking. Cut pasta dough into 10 sheets (approx. 20 x 15 cm) and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ricotta, Mint and Spinach Layer"},{"content":"Place milk in mixing bowl and heat <b>10 min\/80°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add vinegar and heat <b>2 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>. Milk will separate into curds and whey. Leave to rest for 1 minute. <strong><br><\/strong> "},{"content":"Line simmering basket with a nut milk bag or muslin cloth and set over a large bowl. Gently pour ricotta into simmering basket and leave to drain for 15 minutes. Stir through lemon zest and set ricotta aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place mint leaves in mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add spinach leaves and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add salt and reserved ricotta mixture then combine <b>10 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Courgette, Garlic and Pea Layer"},{"content":"Place garlic in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add courgettes and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add oil and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add peas, salt and pepper then mix <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>. <strong><br><\/strong> "},{"content":"Add wine and thyme leaves then cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl. <strong><br><\/strong> "},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Parmesan Béchamel"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C."},{"content":"Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place milk, flour and butter in mixing bowl then cook <b>7 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved grated Parmesan and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"To assemble, cover base of prepared casserole dish or baking tray with 3 pasta sheets, overlapping each sheet slightly. Spread ½ ricotta mixture over the pasta, then place another layer of pasta sheets over the top. Spread ½ courgette mixture over pasta, then top with ¼ béchamel. Place another layer of pasta over top of béchamel and repeat layering process until all ingredients have been used, finishing with a layer of pasta and topped with a layer of béchamel."},{"content":"Bake for 30 minutes (180°C) or until cooked and lightly golden."},{"content":"Season with pepper, garnish with mint leaves and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve lasagne with a fresh green salad.","This light and summery recipe is a great money-saver because you make the pasta and ricotta from scratch.","Roll out small amounts of pasta dough at a time and cover remaining dough with a damp kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out.","For best results after rolling and cutting pasta, allow to dry 1-2 hours on a lightly floured kitchen towel.","After washing and drying the mixing bowl in step 3, you may wish to proceed with step 5 and the preparation of your fillings while the pasta dough rests. <br>","If you have a second Thermomix bowl, it will come in very handy in step 7, as you can insert the simmering basket into it and allow the ricotta to drain. <br>","To increase quantity, add 1 extra egg per additional 100 g flour. The maximum quantity at any one time is 500 g flour and 5 eggs. Increase kneading time to 3 minutes."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","2h","4 portions"]}